<paragraph id="FB3B369AE46D6E374FC8F97DFE87F8B0" blockId="72.[151,1436,1558,1907]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E46D6E374FC8F97DFEADF958" box="[199,283,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Female</emphasis>
—Length ca 
<quantity id="3C7C9B7FE46D6E374EA0F97DFE45F959" box="[431,499,1666,1691]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
, head and mesosoma black with black to brown mesosoma and legs. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E46D6E374A07F97CFA2AF959" box="[1288,1436,1667,1690]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName id="3C844D19E46D6E374A07F97CFA36F959" box="[1288,1408,1667,1690]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E46D6E374A8FF97CFA2AF959" bold="true" box="[1408,1436,1667,1690]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">—</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Scutellum covered in dense yellow hair; tubercle on metanotum minute; propodeal triangle with basal area clearly defined, transverse carina delimiting basal area depressed medially. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E46D6E374C9BF934FBBEF921" box="[916,1032,1739,1762]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Metasoma</emphasis>
—Metasomal foveae not depressed, flush with the surface. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E46D6E374E92F911FE45F8C5" box="[413,499,1774,1799]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Male 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E46D6E374ED8F910FE45F8C5" bold="true" box="[471,499,1775,1798]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">—</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Length ca 
<quantity id="3C7C9B7FE46D6E374D63F911FD04F8C5" box="[620,690,1774,1799]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E46D6E374DB1F911FCA5F8C4" box="[702,787,1774,1799]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Head—</emphasis>
Frons partly or completely covered in dense yellow hair; paraocular area with dense, appressed pale to dark yellow hair. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E46D6E374C64F8ECFC4DF8E9" box="[875,1019,1811,1834]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName id="3C844D19E46D6E374C64F8ECFC69F8E9" box="[875,991,1811,1834]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
Hair of scutum and scutellum dense, orange. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E46D6E374FFEF8C8FEC8F88D" box="[241,382,1847,1870]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Metasoma—</emphasis>
Fovea vaguely indicated; S4 with moderate length fringe. For details of S7–8 and genitalia see figs 127–129.
</paragraph>
